

## **Alternative: Generate PNG Directly**
```python
# Save this as generate_diagram.py
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.patches import FancyBboxPatch
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=(12,8))
ax.axis('off').mmd

# Encoder Box (Blue)
ax.add_patch(FancyBboxPatch((0.1,0.6), 0.3, 0.3, boxstyle="round,pad=0.1", 
                           facecolor='#e3f2fd', edgecolor='#1976d2', linewidth=3))

# Decoder Box (Purple) 
ax.add_patch(FancyBboxPatch((0.6,0.6), 0.3, 0.3, boxstyle="round,pad=0.1",
                           facecolor='#f3e5f5', edgecolor='#7b1fa2', linewidth=3))

ax.text(0.25,0.75,'Encoder',ha='center',va='center',fontsize=14,fontweight='bold')
ax.text(0.75,0.75,'Decoder',ha='center',va='center',fontsize=14,fontweight='bold')

plt.savefig('transformer_fixed.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()


